    <!-- ── Loud Listening ────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="dd-section" id="dd-loudlistening">
      <Fragment set:html={"<span class=\"takeaways-tag\">Love Your Neighbors</span>\n<h1 class=\"takeaways-title\">Loud Listening</h1>\n<p style=\"font-size:.9rem;color:#7A7368;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:2.5rem;font-family:'EB Garamond',serif\">Practical techniques for giving unmistakable attention</p>\n<div class=\"dd-topic-list\"><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-what-it-looks-like\">What It Looks Like</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-what-it-means-to-them\">What It Means to Them</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-quick-start-checklist\">Quick-Start Checklist</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-common-mistakes-to-avoid\">Common Mistakes to Avoid</a></div>\n\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-what-it-looks-like\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">What It Looks Like</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">All-in presence: silence notifications, put phone facedown, swivel toward them, hold the gaze. Multitasking murders connection.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">High-signal body language: lean in, nod every few beats, mirror their excitement or concern. Non-verbal cues carry most of the emotional freight.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Mini verbal check-ins: sprinkle &quot;uh-huh,&quot; &quot;seriously?&quot; or quick paraphrases (&quot;So the flight got canceled right at the gate?&quot;). These micro-bursts prove you&#x27;re tracking.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Follow-up curiosity: when their story pauses, toss a gentle &quot;And then what happened?&quot; or &quot;How did that make you feel?&quot; to keep the narrative flowing.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Reflect a specific detail back to them - not a summary, but one vivid thing they said, which proves you were actually listening.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Seal it with a recap: &quot;Okay, so the plan is brunch at 10 and you&#x27;ll text if plans change-got it!&quot;</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-what-it-means-to-them\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">What It Means to Them</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Feeling truly seen. Brain-imaging studies show that being on the receiving end of active listening lights up the reward circuitry and leaves people with warmer feelings toward the listener.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Faster emotional relief. When someone meets you with big, visible empathy, stress levels drop and they process their own story more clearly.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Deeper trust and closeness. Consistent loud listening cues build the &quot;you get me&quot; bond that turns casual friends into confidants.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-quick-start-checklist\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Quick-Start Checklist</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">1. Park distractions - phone on silent, face down.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">2. Show &amp; tell - nod + a one-word affirmation every 10 seconds or so.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">3. Reflect a detail - &quot;So your boss actually said that?&quot;</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">4. Invite more - &quot;What happened next?&quot;</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">5. Seal it with a recap - &quot;Okay, so the plan is brunch at 10 and you&#x27;ll text if plans change-got it!&quot;</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-common-mistakes-to-avoid\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Common Mistakes to Avoid</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Half-scrolling your phone while they talk. Even a glance at a notification kills the &quot;you get me&quot; bond.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Jumping to solutions before they&#x27;ve finished venting. Sometimes people just need to be heard, not fixed.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">One-upping their story. &quot;Oh that happened to me too, but worse...&quot; makes them feel unseen, not understood.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Waiting for your turn to talk instead of actually absorbing what they&#x27;re saying.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Offering platitudes instead of presence. &quot;Everything happens for a reason&quot; isn&#x27;t listening - it&#x27;s deflecting.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Finishing their sentences. Let the pauses breathe. Silence isn&#x27;t awkward-it&#x27;s where vulnerability lives.</div>\n</div>"} />
    </div>
    <div class="dd-section-divider"></div>

    <!-- ── Gifts ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="dd-section" id="dd-gifts">
      <Fragment set:html={"<span class=\"takeaways-tag\">Love Your Neighbors</span>\n<h1 class=\"takeaways-title\">The Art of Giving Gifts</h1>\n<p style=\"font-size:.9rem;color:#7A7368;font-style:italic;margin-bottom:2.5rem;font-family:'EB Garamond',serif\">Principles, prompts, and specific ideas for every occasion</p>\n<div class=\"dd-topic-list\"><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-gift-giving-principles\">Gift-Giving Principles</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-chatgpt-prompt-for-gift-giving\">ChatGPT Prompt for Gift-Giving</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-situation-specific-gift-ideas\">Situation-Specific Gift Ideas</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-local-care-package-for-someone-who-moved-out-of-state\">Local Care Package</a><a class=\"dd-topic-link\" href=\"#dd-universal-gift-ideas\">Universal Gift Ideas</a></div>\n\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-gift-giving-principles\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Gift-Giving Principles</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Focus on something useful, not flashy. Observe what&#x27;s needed and give something that solves a problem they&#x27;re dealing with.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Gift things that can be used or consumed, like food, alcohol, or a get-well care package.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Skip the pricey gifts. Turn the gift-wrapping paper into a sweet note. Give meaningfully and thoughtfully-i.e. a local care package to a friend who&#x27;s moved away.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Prioritize experiences over things. Organizing a get-together for someone else can be a memorable gift itself.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Give the gift of a lasting memory: an unforgettable trip, a cooking class, concert tickets.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Give when it&#x27;s least expected. Send a book or a paid-for dinner spontaneously &#x27;just because.&#x27; Send flowers and a heartfelt note to someone going through a difficult time.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Give gifts that are explicitly asked for or wanted. Ask someone who knows them what they&#x27;ve had their eye on. Pay attention to the things they buy for themselves.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-chatgpt-prompt-for-gift-giving\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">ChatGPT Prompt for Gift-Giving</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">&quot;I am looking for a gift for my ____ for ____. Ask me several questions to help me determine what might be the best gift to give? After I answer those questions, please come up with several specific ideas or products for me to consider. Please use the gift-giving principles listed below.&quot; [paste principles above]</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-situation-specific-gift-ideas\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Situation-Specific Gift Ideas</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Loss of Job: Second Mountain book, You Are a Badass book, a Starbucks gift card, and a handwritten note.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Someone Who Lost a Spouse or Child: A memory book filled with photos, anecdotes, and memories.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Retirement: A gift certificate for a fun class or workshop.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Change in Health of Family Member: Setting up a meal-train or preparing a home-cooked meal.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">New Home: Toolset or Home Depot gift card. Kitchen gadgets. Cleaning-bucket starter kit. Robot vacuum/mop duo. Custom doormat with family name. Monogrammed throw blanket.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Outstanding Personal Achievement: A thoughtful card and a nice bottle of champagne.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Pregnancy: Maternity clothing subscription box, basket of spicy foods, &#x27;due DATES&#x27; (the fruit), pregnancy massage.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Before Delivery of 2nd+ Child: Send an at-home service to wash and detail their car for the arrival of their next kid.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Cocktail Call-Ahead: Find out where and when someone has dinner reservations, and call the restaurant ahead of time to send a bottle or first cocktail to their table.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">New Parents: Gift of babysitting. Baby&#x27;s breath flowers with a clever note.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Change in Eating Habits: A cookbook focused on their new diet or a meal delivery subscription.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Christmas Approaching: A collection of holiday-themed treats or a hot cocoa set.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Birthday: Happy BDay donuts from Bougie&#x27;s Donuts or Wow Donuts. A gift that brings everyone closer-four tickets to an event, gift card for the gun range, game of golf for two, dance lessons.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Student Studying for Exams: A study care package with healthy snacks, herbal teas, and motivational notes.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Surgery: Task Rabbit or maid service or babysitting vouchers for extra hands.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Third Trimester: &#x27;Due Dates&#x27; (the fruit) with a note: &#x27;Legend has it that dates help encourage babies to make their grand entrance. These might be the only dates you have time for in the next few months!&#x27;</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-local-care-package-for-someone-who-moved-out-of-state\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Local Care Package (for someone who moved out of state)</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Texas Care Package: Salt Lick seasoning, Rudy&#x27;s/Stubbs/Franklins BBQ sauce, Cabo Bob&#x27;s hot sauce, Mateo&#x27;s salsa, Habanero jam, Texas tea recipe with small liquor bottles (Casamigos tequila, Tito&#x27;s vodka, Texas whiskey, gin, simple syrup, lemon juice, coke), Old El Paso taco seasoning, summer sausage with crackers and cheese, Kerbey Lane pancake mix, Shiner beer, Texas Independent beer, Hayley&#x27;s cookies, Texas Two Step popcorn.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"dd-category\" id=\"dd-universal-gift-ideas\"><div class=\"dd-category-title\">Universal Gift Ideas</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Case of beer with a thoughtful note</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Pint of Ben &amp; Jerry&#x27;s</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Ticketmaster or SeatGeek or Eventbrite gift card</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Spa gift card</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Custom calendar using photos and Gen AI</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Visa Debit Card or gift card to their favorite store</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Goldbelly order / Omaha Steaks</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Engraved liquor bottles or customized liquor gift basket</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Food gift basket</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">New dog gifts + Cuddle Clone Stuffed Animals</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Sculpted cakes / Custom cakes</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Cameos</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">New Baby: Custom-made baby blanket embroidered with baby&#x27;s name and birth date</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Starbucks via SMS: &#x27;Sending you some Starbucks love to brighten your day and power you through the next Zoom meeting.&#x27;</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Buy gift cards to their favorite stores. If you don&#x27;t know their favorite store, review their social media or think about what they do for fun.</div>\n<div class=\"dd-item\">Etsy for Christmas and birthdays. Text Georgia, Kate, and Emily for stocking stuffer ideas for Sami each year.</div>\n</div>"} />
